parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Activation of Vehicle Stability Control (VSC) and Traction Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of VSC and traction control can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly, lose steering control, and swerve into oncoming traffic, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The VSC and traction control lights illuminate on the dashboard
accompanied by a loud beeping noise. The vehicle brakes suddenly
and the steering wheel may jerk or pull to one side
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
or pulls to one side. The vehicle may also vibrate or shake while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ABS and brake issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
and the brakes may engage suddenly
causing the vehicle to jerk or lose control.
